REVIEW TYPE AND GOAL\
- Re-review of a code that was already reviewed\
- To see how the author responded to their comments\
\
CONTEXT\
- Project/PR open for around 1 month\
- First bigger contribution of the dev\
\
TRANSCRIPT\
- Checks the original commit\
- Reminding himself of the history of the PR, his own comments\
- Tries to understand the pushed commit by comparing to the previous state, switches to the compare tab window\
- Goes to check previous comments\
- At the bottom of the history, they identified the commit with the biggest bulk of changes by opening it in a new tab.\
- Started going through the code to find a space related to one of his comments from the previous review.\
- The author addressed his comments but the requested documentation was not containing enough of explanation. Reviewer asks if the explanation is documented somewhere else. They ask to document in the discussion where the explanation is located.\
- Resolves a well addressed comment.\
- Double-checks in the code if the comments marked by the author as resolved are actually resolved.\
- While checking, they comment that the author should remember not to put debug statements in committed code\
- Comes back to the discussion history and checks the applied changes comment by comment\
- Tries to scroll several times through the code to figure out whether a comment was addressed.\
- Uses a search function to find the location of the code in question\
- Replies in the discussion that they would appreciate if there would be a note on how the comment was addressed (even though the comment was marked as resolved)\
- When sees that the comment was addressed in the stated way and the code seems to address it, then they mark comment as resolved.\
- Skimms through all the code from top to bottom without the comments\
- Asks to add an explicit statement of the used abbreviation in the doctoring of a class\
- A comment that was not marked as resolved seems to be solved in the code. The reviewer asks to make a further note to address all the similar issues (address all todos) in a follow up actions. Marks the comment as resolved.\
- Marks another addre3ssed comment as resolved after viewing the code to see whether the authors claim was implemented.\
