AFTER THE REVIEW\
- They will have a meeting with the author. If they would not have the study they would probably not pressure themselves to finish he review fully on time before the meeting.\
\
GENERAL STRATEGY\
- Comment by comment they check in the code whether the comments were addressed\
- File by file, they mark when the file is viewed and reviewed to track progress.\
- The process was typical for the projects where they do code review. Then they have other projects where they do not care about doing code reviews or having production quality code. Other scenarios could be to review projects where there is a lot of legacy code.\
- Typically they go through the code looking at the correct implementation of elements, security issues, formatting issues, resolution of previously made comments and improvement of the person who wrote the code.\
- They aimed to teach the author to write production ready code\
- Mentoring students and novices who want to participate in OSS projects is one of the specific goals of the project\
- They think about what he comments on and mentors on on a general level. If they see some issues repeatedly then they might think about how to help the author to improve in a specific area\
- Comments when they see an issue that needs fixing or needs more explanation. When it\'92s asking for improvement, expects change in the code rather than answering a comment.\
- 90% expects to see an action on the code\
- Might also write a comment when sees something particularly nice\
- Code quality is absolutely an inherent part of accepting a pull request\
\
FINISHING A REVIEW\
- when went through all the comments that they made previously, saw all the files, has no pending notes if they made some\
\
UNDERSTANDING\
- Does not reach a full understanding - often sees just smells of issues so they comment on them\
 With the hope that either the author or the reviewer can reach the full understanding of the issue with this additional help.\
- Does not have time to reach that level of understanding.\
- Together with unit tests and criticality of the software this level of understanding is enough. If that would be a nuclear reactor they would try to understand more fully.\
- Full understanding would be an overkill for this context\
